#! /home/user/iverilog-uvm/install/bin/vvp
# Hand-edited VVP reproducer for the of_FORK chunk-boundary bug (Phase 64).
#
# The function body TD_top.boundary_func has 1020 %noop; instructions
# injected between %alloc (slot 1) and %fork (slot 1022 = chunk_size-2).
# With code_chunk_size=1024:
#   thr->pc is pre-incremented to slot 1023 (CHUNK_LINK) before of_FORK.
#   Pre-fix: CHUNK_LINK != JOIN_DETACH -> fork runs sync (wrong).
#   Post-fix: skip CHUNK_LINK -> see slot 1024 = join/detach -> fork async (correct).
# Expected output: PASS chunk_boundary_fork_detach
#
# Run: vvp tests/chunk_boundary_fork_detach.vvp
#
